    "The 'IBM Watson for oncology' software was designed with the objective of making a large impact on personalized treatment plans for cancer patients (Fu et al. 2015).",
    "The software was trained on thousands of clinical and health records of cancer patients, from medical journals, textbooks, and literature curated by the Memorial Sloan Kettering (MSK) cancer center.",
    "This software was determined to make accurate diagnoses and treatment recommendations by identifying related cases from databases of worldwide clinical trials (http:// www. clini caltr ials.",
    "gov) (Bach et al. 2013).",
    "However, a potential disadvantage of this software is its 'bias' towards cancer treatments adopted at the MSK cancer center, possibly resulting in inappropriate recommendations for patients treated elsewhere."
